    <thetext>I am not using Gnome key-ring to manage my passwords.  I use my own home-brew Rube Goldberg system of gpg (not gpg2) scripts.  When presented with a keyring prompt, I cancel out of it.  So, gnome-abrt&apos;s behaviour for me may be different than for the majority of users, for whom this &quot;bug&quot; may or may not exist.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
